==English==
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ri:d/

===Etymology 1===
Old English [[ræd|rǣd]].  Cognate with Dutch [[raad]], German [[Rat]], Swedish [[råd]].

==== Noun====
'''rede''' ''(archaic)''
# [[help]], [[advice]], [[counsel]]
# [[decision]], a [[plan]]

===Etymology 2===
An early form of [[read]].

==== Verb====
'''rede''' ''(archaic except in dialects)'' (past tense/past participle '''red''' or '''redd''')
# to [[govern]], [[protect]]
# to [[discuss]], [[deliberate]]
# to [[advise]]

